 condition=2E My faith in SM has been restored=2E :)

Eric's the easy target, but Kurt's implicated too since it was=
 his lack of firewall configuration which let the P2P work in the=
 first place=2E 

But I don't get the feeling that Kurt was working on his own=
 authority - some management level people may've told him not to=
 initiate a P2P ban on the firewall and to enforce the P2P ban=
 policy=2E (Or he's really missing more clues than we'd expect=
 someone in his position)=2E

I have to wonder though, if the downloading IP really was GB, or=
 if it was spoofed as well in order to frame GB? If Kurt's=
 involved, I think he could've done that - and probably from=
 inside TS's network=2E

Maybe there's someone in management who wants to buy TS and so is=
 trying to torpedo the acquisition? Then there's the funny=
 business with "bulking up" to make the company look more=
 valuable - what if the acquisition's due diligence process would=
 find that not only is TS as much of a bust as GB was, but that=
 there's some criminal activity like embezzlement going on and=
 the manager in question would get found out?


